                <h2 class="section-sub-heading" id="resolution-independent-artwork">Resolution-independent Artwork</h2>
                <p>The actual artwork we generate for comics should be as resolution independent as possible, as well.</p>
                <p>The principal benefit of working in a resolution independent fashion is scalability, or the ability for a piece of artwork to change it size depending on its viewing context, and not lose its crispness and fidelity.</p>
                <p>Additionally, resolution independent artwork allows for much better performance, especially in band with constrained contexts. A piece of vector artwork will download much faster than its raster based counterpart.</p>
                <p>SVG graphics also hold the key here. Much ink based comic art out there today can be expressed as vector rather than raster artwork, by making changes to the artwork creation and production process.</p>
